# Tdarr Media Optimization Environment Configuration
# Copy this file to .env and update the values for your environment

# Timezone
TZ=America/New_York

# Path Configuration
CONFIG_PATH=/mnt/nas/configs/tdarr

# Media library paths (NFS mounts from NAS)
MEDIA_PATH_MOVIES=/mnt/video/Video/Movies
MEDIA_PATH_TV=/mnt/video/Video/TV

# Transcode cache (local disk for temp files)
TRANSCODE_CACHE=/tmp/tdarr

# Secrets (stored in Vaultwarden)
# MONGODB_ROOT_PASSWORD - MongoDB root password (retrieve from Vaultwarden: tdarr-mongodb-root)

# Notes:
# - MEDIA_PATH_MOVIES and MEDIA_PATH_TV should point to your media libraries on NFS
# - CONFIG_PATH stores Tdarr database, configs, and logs
# - TRANSCODE_CACHE uses local disk (/tmp) for transcoding temp files (fast I/O)
# - GPU transcoding requires NVIDIA GPU and nvidia-docker runtime
# - See README.md for scheduling and plugin configuration
